{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund free DNA ancestry tests for Transatlantic Slave Trade Descendants",
        "additional_details": "We think that offering free access to tests could restore cultural and ancestral identity that was forcibly erased during the centuries-long period of slavery. We think this erasure has left millions of descendants disconnected from their lineage, cultural heritage, and geographic origins in Africa.\r\n \r\nOur key reasons for this policy include:\r\nReclaiming Lost History\r\nAddressing Intergenerational Trauma\r\nCultural Empowerment\r\nCorrecting Historical Inequities",
        "background": "The British government played a central role in the transatlantic slave trade.\r\nKey aspects of its involvement:\r\n1. Regulation of the Slave Trade\r\n2. Economic Investment\r\n3. Colonial Exploitation\r\n4. Legal and Military Support\r\n5. Resistance to Abolition",
